The five African National Congress (ANC) supporters and bus driver who died in a crash last Sunday near Modjadjiskloof in Limpopo will be buried on Saturday. The bus was transporting ANC supporters to the party’s provincial birthday celebrations when the driver lost control on the R81 road near Sekgopo village and the bus overturned. Five of the deceased will buried at the Steilloop area. The bus driver will be laid to rest separately at Phola Park in Mokopane. All six were women. They were travelling with other party members to the ANC’s 108 birthday rally. Meanwhile, investigations into allegations of mechanical failure on the bus are underway. Click on the video below: 